    • Field Detail

      • chartRangeClip

        @Option
public Boolean chartRangeClip
        If true then the y values supplied to plot will be clipped to fall between chartRangeMin and chartRangeMax. By default, chartRangeMin/Max just ensure that the chart spans at least that range of values, but do not constrain it.

      • chartRangeMaxX

        @Option
public Double chartRangeMaxX
        Specifies the maximum value to use for the X value of the chart.

      • chartRangeMinX

        @Option
public Double chartRangeMinX
        Specifies the minimum value to use for the X value of the chart.

      • defaultPixelsPerValue

        @Option
public Integer defaultPixelsPerValue
        Defaults pixel width for each value in the chart.

        Default: 3

      • drawNormalOnTop

        @Option
public Boolean drawNormalOnTop
        By default the normal range is drawn behind the fill area of the chart. Setting this option to true causes it to be drawn over the top of the fill area.

      • highlightLineColor

        @Option
public String highlightLineColor
        Specifies a color for the vertical line that appears through a value when moused over.

        Default: "#f22"

      • highlightSpotColor

        @Option
public String highlightSpotColor
        Specifies a color for the spot that appears on a value when moused over.

        Default: "#f5f"

      • lineWidth

        @Option
public Integer lineWidth
        Line width in pixels.

        Default: 1

      • maxSpotColor

        @Option
public String maxSpotColor
        The CSS color of the marker displayed for the maximum value. Set to an empty string to hide it.

      • minSpotColor

        @Option
public String minSpotColor
        The CSS color of the marker displayed for the minimum value. Set to an empty string to hide it.

      • normalRangeMax

        @Option
public Double normalRangeMax
        Threshold value below which to draw a bar to denote the "normal" or expected range of values. For example the green bar here might denote a normal operating temperature range

      • normalRangeMin

        @Option
public Double normalRangeMin
        Threshold value above which to draw a bar to denote the "normal" or expected range of values. For example the green bar here might denote a normal operating temperature range

      • spotColor

        @Option
public String spotColor
        The CSS color of the final value marker. Set to an empty string to hide it.

      • spotRadius

        @Option
public Double spotRadius
        Radius of all spot markers, in pixels. Default: 1.5

      • valueSpots

        @Option
public Map<String,String> valueSpots
        Specifies which points to draw spots on, and with which color. Accepts a range. For example, to render green spots on all values less than 50 and red on values higher use {':49': 'green, '50:': 'red'}.
